Database PG

1.To start Server [sudo docker exec -it myPG psql -U root -d postgres]


2. \l            -- List all databases
   \c dbname     -- Connect to a database
   \du           -- List all users/roles
   \dt           -- List tables in the current database
   \d tablename  -- Show table structure (columns, types, constraints)


3. Total Active connection in postgres:
  SELECT state, count(*)
  FROM pg_stat_activity
  GROUP BY state;

connectionString := "host=localhost port=5432 user=mahid password=root dbname=mydb sslmode=disable"
